        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 13 at 3:57PM MDT by NWS Albuquerque NM</headline>
        <description>At 357 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 6
miles west of Conchas Lake State Park, or 34 miles west of
Tucumcari, moving southeast at 30 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is possible.

Locations impacted include...
Conchas Lake State Park, Conchas and Conchas Dam.

This includes State Road 104 between Mile Markers 55 and 88.

This includes the following recreation areas...
Conchas Dam and Conchas Lake State Park.
</description>
        <instruction>Monitor the weather situation closely and be alert for threatening
weather conditions.

If on or near Conchas Lake, get out of the water and move indoors or
inside a vehicle. Remember, lightning can strike out to 10 miles
from the parent thunderstorm. If you can hear thunder, you are close
enough to be struck by lightning. Move to safe shelter now! Do not
be caught on the water in a thunderstorm.</instruction>
